ABC announced the 100 celebs making up the cast of its "Battle of the Network Stars" revival, which premieres June 29. They'll be divided into 20 teams of five, and hail from shows current and past, including "Modern Family," "Scandal," "Pretty Little Liars," "Law & Order," and "Buffy the Vampire Slayer."

Over 10 episodes, the celeb competitors will participate in games including Tug of War, Dunk Tank, Archery, and Kayak Relay.

Here are the 20 teams (* = returning to "Battle of the Network Stars"):

TV Sitcoms (Bronson Pinchot, Tom Arnold, Dave Coulier, AJ Michalka, Tracey Gold)

vs.

TV Kids (Joey Lawrence, Corbin Bleu, Nolan Gould, *Lisa Whelchel, *Kim Fields)

vs.

vs.
